</p>
<div class="admonition tip"><p class="admonition-title"><span class="fa fa-lightbulb-o"></span> Tip</p><p>if you're using the <code>AbstractFormLoginAuthenticator</code> base class, the
<code>onAuthenticationFailure()</code> method is taken care of for you, but you can override
it if you need to.</p>
</div><p>Of course, you can really use whatever logic you want in here to return a nice message
to the user.</p>
<p>Have fun and give friendly errors!</p>

    
